{
  "texts": [
    "In turn, the algorithm induces an explicit isomorphism between the wild character varieties on both sides of the Fourier transform.",
    "Given an irregular class Θ, we denote by E Θ the associated reduced representation variety, parametrising Stokes local systems with irregular class Θ and a minimal framing (see Definition 3.11).",
    "Theorem 1.2 (see Theorem 5.6).",
    "Let Θ be an irregular class satisfying the above assumptions and let Θ be its formal Fourier transform.",
    "The algorithm induces an algebraic isomorphism between the reduced representation varieties E Θ and E Θ, provided that they are nonempty."
  ]
}